I have a case of a tool: https://github.com/ebi-gene-expression-group/container-galaxy-sc-tertiary/blob/develop/tools/tertiary-analysis/scanpy/scanpy-filter-cells.xml#L31

which gets executed as part of our workflows. When I send it to execute via bioblend invoke_workflow, what I notice is that the parameters map given doesn't get set for the tool on the workflow execution. For the indicated part above we are passing the following element as part of the params dictionary given to invoke workflow:

```
<step_num>: {
"parameters": [
      {
        "__index__": 0,
        "min": "0.0",
        "name": "n_cells",
        "max": "1000000000.0"
      },
      {
        "__index__": 1,
        "min": "0.0",
        "name": "n_counts",
        "max": "1000000000.0"
      }
    ]
}
```

is this how it should be passed for a repeat or I'm missing something? Thanks! This resembles at least the structure I see from the same workflow when shown by bioblend (show workflow). 

The execution doesn't fail, is just that the parameters given are ignored giving preference to the default parameters set in the workflow itself.

Thanks!
